        {
            "endOffset": 99501,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0030",
            "sentence": "Note that the implicit constant in (3.18) may depend on \u03b6.",
            "startOffset": 99443,
            "title": "An auxiliary estimate"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 108984,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0050",
            "sentence": "\u25a1",
            "startOffset": 108983,
            "title": "The major arc"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 85547,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "In Section 4, we show that negligible contributions are obtained from the remainder of the minor and trivial arcs not covered by Corollary 3.6.",
            "startOffset": 85404,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 85148,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "In Section 2, we introduce the preliminary notation required throughout the paper.",
            "startOffset": 85066,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 84433,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "On the major arc, we use Chow's result to obtain the main term in the asymptotic formula, while on the remainder of the minor and trivial arcs, we show that the contribution is negligible.",
            "startOffset": 84245,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 82306,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "We use a dissection of the real line into major, minor and trivial arcs, as is usual in the Davenport\u2013Heilbronn method, to evaluate this integral.",
            "startOffset": 82160,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 82576,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "However, in order to achieve our reduction in the number of variables required, we must also divide our arcs into points with or without good approximations by rationals with small denominators, commonly known as the major and minor arcs in the Hardy\u2013Littlewood method.",
            "startOffset": 82307,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 108982,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0060": {
                    "endOffset": 108981,
                    "startOffset": 108961
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0050",
            "sentence": "This is [6, equation (3.28)].",
            "startOffset": 108953,
            "title": "The major arc"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 85403,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "In Section 3, we present our new estimate for the contribution from the classical Hardy\u2013Littlewood minor arcs, which ultimately allows us to improve on previously known lower bounds for the number of variables required for the asymptotic formula to hold.",
            "startOffset": 85149,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 99343,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0030",
            "sentence": "\u201cShifted Hua's Lemma\u201d",
            "startOffset": 99322,
            "title": "An auxiliary estimate"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 84623,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "In order to do this, we make use of the measure of the set of points with good rational approximations, noting that these points constitute only a small fraction of any given unit interval.",
            "startOffset": 84434,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 87690,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0020",
            "sentence": "\u25a1",
            "startOffset": 87689,
            "title": "Preliminary notation"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 105496,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0040",
            "sentence": "\u25a1",
            "startOffset": 105495,
            "title": "The minor and trivial arcs"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 84009,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "We make use of a variant of Theorem 1.2 (see Theorem 3.1, and the subsequent conclusion in Corollary 3.6), which provides a key input to our application of Freeman's variant of the Davenport\u2013Heilbronn method.",
            "startOffset": 83801,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 85870,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "The author would like to thank Trevor Wooley for his supervision and for suggesting this line of research, and Sam Chow for helpful conversations.",
            "startOffset": 85724,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 85724,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "In Section 5 we present a result of Chow on the major arc, giving the main term in the asymptotic formula for the number of solutions, thus completing the proof of Theorem 1.1.",
            "startOffset": 85548,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 105494,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0010": {
                    "endOffset": 105493,
                    "startOffset": 105479
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0040",
            "sentence": "This is [1, Lemma 4.4].",
            "startOffset": 105471,
            "title": "The minor and trivial arcs"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 87688,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0060": {
                    "endOffset": 87687,
                    "startOffset": 87673
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0020",
            "sentence": "This is a special case of [6, Lemma 2.2].",
            "startOffset": 87647,
            "title": "Preliminary notation"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 82159,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "To prove our result, we approximate the number of solutions to (1.2) by a certain integral over the real line (see Section 2 for details).",
            "startOffset": 82021,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 84244,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "The number of variables required to achieve this estimate is smaller than that required by Chow to bound the contribution from points on the minor and trivial arcs, and this enables us to make our improvement as stated in Theorem 1.1.",
            "startOffset": 84010,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 85065,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "We now present a brief outline of the structure of the remainder of this paper.",
            "startOffset": 84986,
            "title": "Introduction"
        }
